definition.value: An acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of isotridecanoyl-CoA.

A hydrochloride obtained by combining procarbazine with one equivalent of hydrochloric acid. An antineoplastic chemotherapy drug used for treatment of Hodgkin's lymphoma. Metabolism yields azo-procarbazine and hydrogen peroxide, which results in the breaking of DNA strands.
A ketoaldonic acid obtained formally by deamination of neuraminic acid. Although not containing nitrogen it is regarded as being a member of the sialic acid family.
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of 3-oxoisopentadecanoyl-CoA.
An organic cation that is the conjugate acid of procarbazine.
Deaminoneuraminic acid in which the anomric configuration is alpha.
A methyl-branched fatty acyl-CoA obtained from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of isopalmitic acid
An amino trisaccharide consisting of alpha-KDN, beta-D-galactose and N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residues linked sequentially (2->3) and (1->3).
An 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-hydroxyisopentadecanoyl-CoA; the major species at pH 7.3.
A methyl-branched fatty acyl-CoA obtained from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-oxoisooctadecanoic acid.
A methyl-branched fatty acyl-CoA obtained from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of isotridecanoic acid
A linear amino trisaccharide consisting of alpha-KDN, beta-D-galactose and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues linked sequentially (2->3) and (1->3).
A methyl-branched fatty acyl-CoA obtained from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-oxoisopentadecanoic acid.

A branched amino tetrasaccharide consisting of alpha-KDN, beta-D-galactose and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues linked sequentially (2->3) and (1->4), with an alpha-L-fucose residue linked (1->3) to the N-acetyl-D-glucosamine at the reducing end.
A linear trisaccharide consisting of alpha-KDN, beta-D-galactose and D-glucosamine residues linked sequentially (2->3) and (1->4).
A linear amino trisaccharide consisting of alpha-KDN, beta-D-galactose and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues linked sequentially (2->3) and (1->4).
A methyl-branched fatty acyl-CoA obtained from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-hydroxyisopentadecanoic acid.
A linear amino trisaccharide consisting of alpha-KDN, beta-D-galactose and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues linked sequentially (2->6) and (1->4).
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of 3-oxoisoheptadecanoyl-CoA.
An acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-hydroxyisoheptadecanoyl-CoA.

An amino oligosaccharide (tetradecasaccharide) consisting of three trisaccharide units, each consisting of two beta-D-galactose residues and one N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue all linked (1->4), two of the units of which are linked (1->2) and (1->4) to a single alpha-D-mannose residue and the other linked (1->2) to another alpha-D-mannose residue, with the two mannose residues being linked (1->3) and (1->6) to the mannose residue of an amino trisaccharide comprising beta-D-mannose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues all linked (1->4).
A long-chain unsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of hexadec-9-enoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An amino trisaccharide comprised of two beta-D-galactose residues linked (1->4), with the one at the reducing end being linked (1->4) to an N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residue.
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of 3-oxodocosanoyl-CoA; principal microspecies at pH 7.3.

An amino oligosaccharide (dodecasaccharide) consisting of two tetrasaccharide units, each consisting of two beta-D-galactose residues, one N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue and one alpha-L-mannose residue linked in sequence (1->4), (1->4) and (1->2), linked (1->2) and (1->6) to the mannose residue of an amino trisaccharide comprising beta-D-mannose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues all linked (1->4), and to the reducing-end N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residue of which is also linked (1->6) an alpha-L-fucosyl residue.
A methyl-branched fatty acyl-CoA obtained from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-oxoisoheptadecanoic acid.

An amino oligosaccharide (dodecasaccharide) consisting of two tetrasaccharide units, each consisting of two beta-D-galactose residues, one N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue and one alpha-L-mannose residue linked in sequence (1->4), (1->4) and (1->2), linked (1->2) and (1->6) to the mannose residue of an amino trisaccharide comprising beta-D-mannose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues all linked (1->4).
A 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of 3-hydroxyicosanoyl-CoA.
A 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of 3-hydroxydocosanoyl-CoA.

A pentacyclic triterpenoid that is ursa-12,20(30)-diene substituted by a carboxy group at position 28 and hydroxy groups at positions 2, 3 and 23. It is a phytoalexin isolated from the peel of unripe kiwi fruit Actinidia deliciosa.

An amino oligosaccharide (heptadecasaccharide) in which two alpha-D-mannose residues, each of which has linked to it a trisaccharide sequence of two beta-D-galactose residues and an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue, are linked (1->4) and (1->6) to the mannose residue of a trisaccharide sequence of beta-D-mannose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues all linked (1->4).
A trans-2,3-didehydroacyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of (E)-isopentadec-2-enoyl-CoA. Major species at pH 7.3.
A saturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of isoheptadecanoyl-CoA. Major species at pH 7.3.
A 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (E)-isoheptadec-2-enoyl-CoA.
A lipid A oxoanion obtained via deprotonation of the carboxy, phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of lipid A-core 1-diphosphate.
An N-(long-chain-acyl)ethanolamine that is the ethanolamide of palmitic (hexadecanoic) acid.
An N-acylethanolamine 16:1 that is the ethanolamide of palmitoleic acid.
An N-(long-chain-acyl)ethanolamine that is the ethanolamide of oleic acid. The monounsaturated analogue of the endocannabinoid anandamide.
An N-acylethanolamine 20:5 that is the ethanolamide of (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z17Z)-eicosapentaenoic acid.
A pentacyclic triterpenoid that belongs to the group of D:C-friedooleanane type triterpenoids.
A branched mannooligosaccharide comprised of nine alpha-D-mannose residues configured as shown in the diagram.
An oligosaccharide compound consisting of nine glycosyl residues.
A branched mannooligosaccharide comprised of eight alpha-D-mannose residues arrangedin the configuration shown.
An alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-D-Manp in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has alpha- configuration.

An EC 2.3.1.* (acyltransferase transferring other than amino-acyl group) inhibitor that interferes with the action of fatty acid synthase (EC 2.3.1.85), a multi-enzyme protein involved in fatty acid synthesis.
A ribonucleoside triphosphate oxoanion that is the heptaanion of guanosine 3'-diphosphate 5'-triphosphate.

A mannopentaose comprised of a chain of three alpha-D-mannose residues linked (1->2) and (1->3), with a further two-D-mannose-residue (1->2)-linked unit linked (1->6) to the mannose residue at the reducing end.
A linear mannotriose in which three alpha-D-mannose residues are linked in sequence (1->2) and (1->3).
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of (8Z,11Z,14Z)-3-oxoicosa-8,11,14-trienoyl-CoA.

alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc in which the anomeric configuration at the reducing-end GlcNAc residue is beta.
